173
00:12:40.740 --> 00:12:42.914
It's cheaper than I thought.

174
00:12:42.914 --> 00:12:46.576
But I don't have a reason
to wear it, so it's a waste for me.

175
00:12:46.576 --> 00:12:50.306
- Is that shop hard to find?
- It's right behind the hotel.

176
00:12:50.306 --> 00:12:53.630
Take the back door, turn left, take
the first alleyway and walk one minute.

177
00:12:53.630 --> 00:12:55.673
It's close. That's a relief.

178
00:12:55.673 --> 00:13:00.042
Another tourist from
the last group bought five of them.

179
00:13:00.042 --> 00:13:03.000
- It was for her friend's wedding.
- Amazing.

180
00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:06.365
There must have been a lot of tension.
You know how it is among friends.

181
00:13:06.365 --> 00:13:09.836
You're right. There's always that
one friend you can't stand.

182
00:13:09.836 --> 00:13:13.476
You have to look prettier
when they get married.

183
00:13:13.476 --> 00:13:14.768
You're right.

184
00:13:17.629 --> 00:13:20.106
Women become friends so easily.

185
00:13:20.106 --> 00:13:23.298
I know, right? Isn't it fascinating?

186
00:13:23.837 --> 00:13:26.186
Look at her excitement.

187
00:13:27.394 --> 00:13:29.481
Your girlfriend is beautiful.

188
00:13:29.481 --> 00:13:33.062
Pardon? Your girlfriend is beautiful too.

189
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:34.480
Thank you.

190
00:13:37.989 --> 00:13:40.683
- Pardon?
- Pardon?

191
00:13:47.787 --> 00:13:49.822
- You were in the search forces, right?
- Yes.

192
00:13:49.822 --> 00:13:52.778
- In the army forces?
- No, in the 505 special forces.

193
00:13:52.778 --> 00:13:54.856
505...

194
00:13:54.856 --> 00:13:56.962
- Below the mountain?
- You know?

195
00:13:56.962 --> 00:14:01.370
Of course! If you head toward Seoul from
there, there's an industrial complex.

196
00:14:01.370 --> 00:14:03.745
- Yes, there is.
- That's where I was.

197
00:14:03.745 --> 00:14:05.293
With 505...

198
00:14:05.293 --> 00:14:08.865
Men become friends so easily.

199
00:14:08.865 --> 00:14:11.927
I know, right? Isn't it fascinating?

200
00:14:11.927 --> 00:14:13.318
Then...

201
00:14:15.794 --> 00:14:17.825
What do you think they're doing?

202
00:14:18.565 --> 00:14:22.614
I'm not even curious.
He's so frustrating.

203
00:14:22.614 --> 00:14:25.918
But your boyfriend is very handsome.

204
00:14:25.918 --> 00:14:31.169
He's not that handsome.
Your boyfriend is much more handsome.

205
00:14:31.169 --> 00:14:33.301
I don't have a boyfriend.

206
00:14:34.346 --> 00:14:36.756
I'll call you if I can't find the shop.

207
00:14:41.395 --> 00:14:43.307
I can't believe I met you here.

208
00:15:20.865 --> 00:15:24.048
This is the Pont Neuf bridge
which was in the movie

209
00:15:24.048 --> 00:15:26.323
"The Lovers on the Bridge."

210
00:15:26.323 --> 00:15:29.417
"Pont" means bridge,
and "Neuf" means new.

211
00:15:29.417 --> 00:15:31.888
So it means "new bridge."

212
00:15:32.465 --> 00:15:37.490
I think "Pont Neuf" is a word that
completes the romance of Paris.

213
00:15:38.116 --> 00:15:42.222
Take a leisurely stroll, have a chat

214
00:15:42.222 --> 00:15:46.582
and talk about why
you came here on vacation.

215
00:15:57.443 --> 00:15:59.039
Yes, Big Brother.

216
00:16:00.736 --> 00:16:03.368
Pardon? Today?

217
00:16:07.263 --> 00:16:09.898
Yes, thank you. Yes, have a good night.

218
00:16:09.898 --> 00:16:11.663
Yes. Yes.

219
00:16:12.929 --> 00:16:15.724
So Ran, the investment decision
will be made today.

220
00:16:15.724 --> 00:16:19.721
I passed the final round.
All that's left is the CEO's approval.

221
00:16:20.739 --> 00:16:22.519
Then it's not decided yet.

222
00:16:22.519 --> 00:16:25.967
It's pretty much decided.
The CEO's approval is just a formality.

223
00:16:25.967 --> 00:16:29.168
Okay, I really hope it works out.

224
00:16:29.168 --> 00:16:31.942
Geez, can't you be happy with me?

225
00:16:31.942 --> 00:16:33.917
I'm happy.

226
00:16:33.917 --> 00:16:36.889
So Ran, I'll do a good job.

227
00:16:36.889 --> 00:16:38.490
I'll do a really good job.

228
00:16:38.490 --> 00:16:44.198
I'll only put business cards that I'll
keep for years in the wallet you gave me.

229
00:16:44.821 --> 00:16:46.451
I'll stick to it.

230
00:16:48.928 --> 00:16:50.289
Okay.

231
00:16:57.350 --> 00:17:01.530
<i>[2,555 days]</i>

232
00:17:01.530 --> 00:17:04.605
<i>[Seven years]</i>

233
00:17:17.599 --> 00:17:20.960
<i>It's been around 27 or 28 years
since we got together.</i>

234
00:17:27.116 --> 00:17:30.844
<i>I wasn't in the best situation,
so you had a hard time.</i>

235
00:17:32.586 --> 00:17:35.066
<i>I know you had a hard time.</i>

236
00:17:43.038 --> 00:17:46.874
You're driving me crazy.
Is this a coffee shop?

237
00:17:46.874 --> 00:17:49.758
Why did you bring coffee machines
into this restaurant?

238
00:17:49.758 --> 00:17:53.395
Americano with chicken?
It looks like we'll be on the news!

239
00:17:53.395 --> 00:17:57.134
A cup of coffee after a meal
would be so nice.

240
00:17:57.134 --> 00:17:59.987
This alone will make us
100 million won a month.

